The `\draw` command is used to draw lines between the pieces, and the `\node` command is used to add the piece symbols to their respective positions. Note that the FEN notation used here represents a standard starting position for White, with the pieces arranged as follows:
- rNBQKbnR (white rook)
- pppppp (eight white pawns)
- nBRc (white knight)
- ppPPP (seven white pawns)
- bKNRQ (black king)
- pppppp (eight black pawns)

